description: President Donald Trump is bringing his own form of brash showmanship to immigration policy.
title: Trump Deploys Visible Military Force to Launch Migrant Crackdown

description: Slovakia’s second-biggest governing party expelled two members who demanded posts in the administration, raising the question of whether the coalition still controls a majority in parliament.
title: Slovak Coalition’s Majority Faces Test as Two Lawmakers Expelled

description: This is Washington Edition, the newsletter about money, power and politics in the nation’s capital. Every Friday, White House correspondent Akayla Gardner delivers a roundup of the key news and events in politics, policy and economics that you need to know.  Sign up here and follow us at @bpolitics. Email our editors here.
title: Trump Heads to Nevada, Highlighting His No-Tax-on-Tips Promise

description: The US Supreme Court accepted a major new church-state showdown, agreeing to consider whether states with public charter schools are constitutionally required to approve and fund religious institutions as part of the taxpayer-supported program.
title: Supreme Court to Weigh Tax-Supported Religious School Case

description: Secretary of State Marco Rubio, a longtime China hawk, expressed concern about Beijing’s coercive behavior against Taiwan and aggression in the South China Sea in his first formal call with Chinese Foreign Minister Wang Yi on Friday, a sign that the US-China relationship could get turbulent.
title: Rubio Stresses ‘America First’ in Call With China’s Wang Yi

description: President Donald Trump’s Environmental Protection Agency is considering rescinding California’s permission to tackle climate change through stringent automobile pollution limits, the administration said in a US Supreme Court filing.
title: EPA Revisiting California Emissions Curbs, Trump Official Says

description: Canada is planning to set up a center to accommodate migrants from the US crossing the northern border into Quebec as the Trump administration pushes ahead with an immigration crackdown.
title: Canada Eyes New Hub to Handle Possible Refugee Surge From US

description: A cornerstone of President Donald Trump’s bid to reshape the US immigration system has run into an early roadblock: an octogenarian federal judge in Seattle.

description: Slovak Prime Minister Robert Fico faced nationwide demonstrations against his increasing pivot toward Vladimir Putin’s Russia, including calls for his resignation in one of the country’s biggest protests since the fall of communism.

description: The eastern Democratic Republic of Congo has been gripped by years of conflict that have displaced millions of people. The start of 2025 marked an escalation of the violence as rebels aligned with Rwanda closed in on a key Congolese trading hub, threatening to trigger an all-out war between the two central African neighbors.
title: How Rebel Advances in Congo Threaten War With Rwanda

description: The Ukrainian Defense Ministry fired the director of the Ukrainian Defense Procurement Agency, Maryna Bezrukova, because of unsatisfactory results in timely deliveries of weapons for the army, Defense Minister Rustem Umerov said in a post on Facebook.

description: Brazil’s government will cut some import taxes and eschew both price controls and the use of fiscal measures as it rushes to lower food costs, a top cabinet official said Friday.

description: The European Union is unlikely to propose phasing out Russian liquefied natural gas as part of a new package of sanctions targeting Moscow for its invasion of Ukraine, according to people familiar with the matter.

description: The Trump administration began sending deportees on US military planes back to Guatemala and El Salvador, according to people familiar with the matter, as it looks to demonstrate that it’s acting on campaign promises to return millions of migrants to their home countries.

description: A federal judge on Friday barred the founder of the Oath Keepers extremist group and several associates convicted in the Jan. 6, 2021, attack from entering Washington — or the US Capitol building — without his permission first.
title: Jan. 6 Convicts Freed by Trump Barred From US Capitol by Judge

description: President Donald Trump said he would feel no responsibility if Anthony Fauci or John Bolton were attacked after he moved to strip their government security in the opening days of his presidential term.

description: Hamas named four Israeli women soldiers it plans to release from captivity in a second hostage-for-prisoner swap, as the Gaza ceasefire nears the end of its first week.

description: Norway’s prime minister is trying to resolve a feud with his key coalition partner to avert a political crisis with seven months to go until the next parliamentary elections.

description: China’s top diplomat spoke with Secretary of State Marco Rubio in a phone call Friday, despite the former Republican senator still being under Beijing’s sanctions.

description: President Donald Trump vowed to rebuild communities in North Carolina ravaged by hurricanes last year during his first trip outside Washington of his second term, saying he would ask Congress to provide additional funding for clean-up efforts.

description: Howard Lutnick, President Donald Trump’s nominee to lead the Commerce Department, detailed his wealth and influence across hundreds of firms and left open the possibility of his adult children buying his holdings if he wins confirmation.

description: The US Federal Trade Commission is likely to have bipartisan support to keep filing cases to block anticompetitive mergers under the Trump administration, said Henry Liu, the outgoing director of the agency’s Bureau of Competition.

description: President Donald Trump’s blitz of executive actions align with many of the ideas promoted in a conservative policy blueprint he once distanced himself from.

description: President Donald Trump said he’d prefer not to have to impose tariffs on China, while at the same time highlighting the influence he sees his threats having over the Asian nation’s actions.

When it comes to restricting work visas for highly-skilled foreigners, a goal Trump pursued in his first presidency from 2017 to 2021, those in his inner circle are sharply divided. title: Why Trump’s Inner Circle Is So Divided on H-1B Visas

description: Edison International’s Southern California Edison utility said that a vehicle struck and damaged a utility pole, resulting in a circuit relay shortly before the start of the Laguna Fire in Ventura County, California.

description: California Governor Gavin Newsom greeted Donald Trump’s inauguration Monday with a gesture of conciliation toward the new president, noting the need for partnership and mutual respect.
